    "body": "I'm going to declare victory here, because the `RustcFlags` data type is exposed and once you've built a context (using a rustpkg API function), you can replace it with a `RustcFlags` of your own construction. I'm sure there are nicer ways, but I'll close this until someone has a concrete proposal for an improvement.\n",
